  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### (E) Another thing that comes up a lot with array shapes is thinking about how to aggregate over specific dimensions. Figure out how the NumPy sum function works (and the axis argument in particular).\n",
    "### Write code to do the following:\n",
    "1. **Sum baz over its second dimension and print the result.**\n",
    "2. **Sum baz over its third dimension and print the result.**\n",
    "3. **Sum baz over both its first and third dimensions and print the result.**\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 210,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Sum baz over its second dimension:\n",
      " [[ 13  25]\n",
      " [ 70  75]\n",
      " [120 125]]\n",
      "Sum baz over its third dimension:\n",
      " [[ 1  5  9  6 17]\n",
      " [21 25 29 33 37]\n",
      " [41 45 49 53 57]]\n",
      "Sum baz over both its first and third dimensions:\n",
      " [ 63  75  87  92 111]\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "print(\"Sum baz over its second dimension:\\n\",np.sum(baz, axis=1))\n",
    "print(\"Sum baz over its third dimension:\\n\", np.sum(baz, axis=2))\n",
    "print(\"Sum baz over both its first and third dimensions:\\n\",np.sum(baz, axis=(0, 2)))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### (F) Along with shaping and indexing, we also do a lot of slicing which is where you index with ranges to get subvectors and sometimes submatrices. \n",
    "### Write code to do the following:\n",
    "1. **Slice out the second row of bar and print it.**\n",
    "2. **Slice out the last column of bar using the -1 notation and print it.**\n",
    "3. **Slice out the top right 2 × 2 submatrix of bar and print it.**"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 211,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Slice out the second row of bar:\n",
      " [-1  7  8  9 10 11]\n",
      "Slice out the last column of bar using the -1 notation:\n",
      " [[ 5]\n",
      " [11]\n",
      " [17]\n",
      " [23]\n",
      " [29]]\n",
      "Slice out the top right 2 × 2 submatrix of bar and print it:\n",
      " [[ 4  5]\n",
      " [10 11]]\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "print(\"Slice out the second row of bar:\\n\",bar[1, :])\n",
    "print(\"Slice out the last column of bar using the -1 notation:\\n\",bar[:, -1].reshape(5,1))\n",
    "print(\"Slice out the top right 2 × 2 submatrix of bar and print it:\\n\",bar[:2, -2:])\n"
   ]
  },
